    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jc.00448_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name> 
                    <date when="1887-07-03">Sunday forenoon July 3</date> 
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Am feeling poorly to-day&#8212;the result of the long spell of hot weather&#8212;(two
                poor little babies have died from it in this block the last week)&#8212;I send you
                and George a nice little copy of "Specimen Days"<ptr target="loc.03886_n3"/>&#8212;</p>
            <p>&#8212;Love to you all&#8212;</p>
            <p>&#8212;If the weather changes, &#38; I feel better I sh'd like to drive down &#38; stay five
                or six hours, some day early the coming week&#8212;</p>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jc.00449_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="left" resp="#ww">Mrs. Susan Stafford Glendale New Jersey</note>
        </body>
    </text>
